26/11/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police announced on Wednesday (November 25th) they have intercepted 44kg of high-quality heroin allegedly destined for the Italian market.
The heroin is worth more than 2m euros.
Police say they found it Tuesday night in a truck travelling from Turkey, via Greece.
Eight Macedonian citizens were arrested.
Weapons and ammunitions were seized as well.
(Makfax, A1, MIA - 25/11/09)
